cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DB

The paper presents a novel approach for analyzing educational records using matrix factorization and temporal course-wise influence for grade prediction. This involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
